# Never copy these into the Docker image

node_modules
# Why: Docker installs fresh dependencies inside the container.
# Copying node_modules from host wastes space and can cause
# platform conflicts (Mac vs Linux binaries are different)

.env
# Why: .env contains passwords and secrets. Never bake
# secrets into an image — they become visible to anyone
# who pulls the image from Docker Hub

npm-debug.log
# Why: Debug logs are useless inside a container
# and just add unnecessary size

.git
# Why: Git history has no place in a production image
# Can also expose sensitive commit history
